Step 1: Calculate the Quick Assets.
• Quick Assets include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable.
  Cash on Hand = 4,058,544.03  
  Bank Deposits = 3,079,000.00  
  Accounts Receivable = 2,984,071.72  
  Interest Receivable = 13,279.60  
  Sum of Quick Assets = 4,058,544.03 + 3,079,000.00 + 2,984,071.72 + 13,279.60  
                   = 10,134,894.35

Step 2: Identify the Current Liabilities.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 624,988.48

Step 3: Compute the Quick Ratio.
  Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
         = 10,134,894.35 / 624,988.48  
         ≈ 16.22

Step 4: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement:
  Net Profit = 1,903,401.82  
  Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51  
  Net Profit Margin = (1,903,401.82 / 4,879,769.51) × 100%
          ≈ 0.3899 × 100%  
          ≈ 38.99%

Thus, the final solution is:

{"solution": {"Quick Ratio": "16.22", "Net Profit Margin": "38.99%"}}
